-- Italy Plans to Sell Bonds Indexed to 6-Month Euribor Via Bank Syndicate
-- Paul Dobson
-- 2010-06-17T17:34:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/italy-plans-to-sell-bonds-indexed-to-6-month-euribor-via-bank-syndicate.html

          
          
             Italy said it plans to sell new
floating-rate bonds with semi-annual coupons indexed to the six-
month euribor.  
 The nation will initially sell the securities via banks,
with a seven-year maturity, the Italian debt agency said in a
presentation on its  website .  
